# Security Rules

## Purpose
Implement controls in `docs/SECURITY.md` — tenant isolation, auth, OWASP mitigations.

## Requirements
- JWT RS256 access tokens 15min; refresh rotation with reuse detection.
- bcrypt cost 12 for passwords; lockout after 5 failed attempts.
- RBAC on every protected route; field-level DTO stripping by role.
- Rate limiting on auth and public endpoints.
- Razorpay webhooks: HMAC verify + idempotency.
- Secrets in AWS Secrets Manager only — never commit `.env` secrets.
- Audit log for auth events, deletes, impersonation, billing changes.

## Restrictions
- No `eval`, no dynamic SQL concatenation.
- No logging passwords, tokens, full PAN/Aadhaar.
- No CORS `*` in production.
- No disabling CSRF protections on cookie auth routes without review.

## Best Practices
- Security headers via middleware (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options).
- Dependabot + npm audit in CI.
- Tenant isolation integration tests on every repo-touching PR.

## Anti-Patterns
- Trusting `tenant_id` from client body.
- Returning 403 with "exists in other tenant" messages.
- Storing refresh tokens plaintext in DB.

## Examples

```typescript
// GOOD: Tenant scoped lookup
const property = await repo.findOne({ id, tenantId: ctx.tenantId });
if (!property) throw new NotFoundException();
```
